WEBVTT

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:31.816
His research concluded

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:35.336
that people would be satisfied

00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:37.296
with the judge's rulings,

00:03:37.320 --> 00:03:39.336
even when the judge ruled against them,

00:03:39.360 --> 00:03:41.936
if they perceived
that they were treated fairly

00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:43.840
and with dignity and respect.

00:03:44.440 --> 00:03:47.456
And that perception of fairness
begins with what?

00:03:47.480 --> 00:03:51.680
Begins with how judges speak
to court participants.

00:03:52.960 --> 00:03:54.336
Now, being a judge

00:03:54.360 --> 00:04:00.336
is sometimes like having
a reserve seat to a tragic reality show